			This brought me to the Pro Dive diving base after Coogee. The journey only lasted 5 minutes and cost an impressive $ 37. </p>
		<p> After checking in, we started to Gordons Bay, my absolute favorite diving area. It is a small bay north of Coogee Beach, with an underwater path that can be followed as a diver. There I learned diving in 2013 and I am very happy that I was allowed to dive there today. </p>
		<p> The first dive was already awesome. We went in for six plus guides and slid along the path. After we came to a small steep wall, we turned right and swam away from the path. At the beginning I was at the end of the group and a little disappointed because I couldn't see as much fish as I remembered. After the fins of other divers also plagued me twice, I decided to swim forward and give my luck with nature a chance next to the guide. After a few minutes, my eyes adjusted to the fish here. There was a lot to see. You just have to look. I saw a lot of different ways. From spherical fishing to Tiegernroche and stone fishing to entire swarms of silver -yellow butterfish. Even a turtle was seen for a short time. Unfortunately, the dive was over after 50 minutes. I still had almost half a bottle of air left. :( </p>
