        <p> The second dive was even more impressive. Now that my eyes were already set to the fish world here, I got a lot to see from the start. Unfortunately, the water was quite cool for my hot water suit at about 13m depth with only 19 degrees. But we even got to see an approx. 1.20m long shark. On the way back I would have loved to stay in the water for 2 - 5 more hours, because when I got out there was so much fish that I didn't even know where to look first. </p>
		<p> I also treated myself to a taxi for the way back to the hotel. This time the trip lasted about 25 minutes and only cost $ 28 for it. I fear that the driver this morning ripped me off completely. </p>
		<p> We spent the evening again at the Vivid Festival in downtown Sydney. Today we finally wanted to see the opera. On the way through the gorges of the high -rise buildings. When we passed the Skytower, we decided to go up spontaneously and to look at Sydney from above after sunset. The view was like 4 years ago, the hammer. I can do what I want, but I think this city is great. I didn't like the thought at all, not to know if or when I would come back here. </p>
		<p> After 2 quick rounds over the viewing platform we drove down again, because we also wanted to see the many colorful lights up close. First we came to Martin Place. There was really a lot of light and art built there. We liked a video projection best that was adapted directly to the shape of a building. To see there was a multi -minute animation about a frog and where it came over anywhere. </p>
		<p> Then we went towards the botanical garden. Unfortunately, it was only so full that we decided to run directly to the harbor basin and visit the garden on another day. Once at the harbor, there were also a lot of visitors there. However, since the organizers had built up fences again and steered the river of the visitors with a lot of staff, the whole thing was quite pleasant and cozy. Shortly before the opera it got too crowded and we turned and went to the other side of the harbor basin. In the art museum there, we finally faith. Canon had set up an armada of printers there and everyone who wanted could have pictures printed up to size A2 ... free of charge !!! In addition, Canon also offered workshops on various topics several times in the evening. And if you don't have a decent equipment, you could even borrow this free of charge for the workshops. We took the chance and had a picture printed in A3. </p>
		<p> When the printer was finished, we always went along the harbor basin in search of the best position to take photos of the animated opera. In the end there were definitely over 300 photos. In addition, we will have passed swings, which performed a show independently every 20 minutes and served perfectly as a photo motif. We will also pick up a pressure from Canon tomorrow. </p>
		<p> Then it went back towards the accommodation. After midnight we finally fully exhausted to bed. </p>
